Create dummy data for testing the fall enrollment functions

Source: R/create_dummy_data_ef1.R
create_dummy_data_ef1.Rd

Creates students and retention dataframes for use in parts A, B, C, D, E, and G. Student-faculty ratio (part G) will ask for a number when the function is run and does not need to exist here. To create both dataframes, run the function twice with different arguments, and save results into separate objects.

create_dummy_data_ef1(df_type = "students", n = 100)

Arguments

df_type

A string with the dummy data requested ("students" for parts A-D & G or "retention" for part E)

n

A number

Value

A text file
